{{environmentalist-stub}}

'''Engine power''' or '''horsepower''' is the maximum [[power (physics)|power]] that an engine can put out. It can be expressed in [[kilowatt]]s or [[horsepower]]. The power output depends on the size and design of the engine, but also on the speed at which it is running and the [[mechanical load|load]] or [[torque]]. Maximum power is achieved at relatively high speeds and at high load.
