{{Infobox power station | name = Highland Wind Project | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Iowa | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|43|05|N|95|34|W|region:US-IA_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = United States | location = [[O'Brien County, Iowa|O'Brien]] county in [[Iowa]] | status = mostly operational | construction_began = 2013 | commissioned = 2015 | decommissioned = | cost = about $1 billion | owner = [[MidAmerican Energy Company]] | operator = [[MidAmerican Energy Company]] | ps_units_operational = 218 | ps_units_manu_model = Siemens 2.3 MW | wind_hub_height = | wind_rotor_diameter = | wind_rated_speed = | wind_farm_type = | wind_site_elevation = | wind_site_usage = | wind_site_area = | ps_electrical_capacity = 502 MW | ps_electrical_cap_fac = 36-40+<ref>{{cite web|work=Iowa Utilities Board Docket No.: RPU-2003-0003|publisher=[[Iowa Utilities Board]]|accessdate=9 May 2014}}</ref> | website = | extra = Largest in state when completed. }} The '''Highland Wind Project''' is a large [[wind power]] project in [[O'Brien County, Iowa]]. The 500 MW project was placed online in 2015.
==Project== The project is part of $1.9 billion in wind power construction announced by [[MidAmerican Energy]] in 2013. The project is the largest in Iowa, as well as the largest single-phase project in the world. Siemens is supplying 218 2.3 MW wind turbines for the project.<ref>{{cite web|title=MidAmerican begins construction on Iowa’s largest wind project|url=http://www.power-eng.com/articles/2013/12/midamerican-begins-construction-on-iowa-s-largest-wind-project.html|publisher=Power Engineering|accessdate=9 May 2014}}</ref>
The project is located at the southern end of [[Buffalo Ridge]]. The proposed [[Rock Island Clean Line]] [[HVDC]] transmission line would originate just north of the project.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://siouxcityjournal.com/news/local/a1/wind-energy-boom-blows-into-northwest-iowa-county/article_90aa0dbf-752a-5384-81b1-82b3662271d4.html|title=Wind energy boom blows into Northwest Iowa county|work=Sioux City Journal}}</ref>
An expansion of the project, formerly known as Highland II was developed by Invenergy.<ref>{{cite web|title=O'Brien County's 2nd major wind farm on fast track|url=http://www.chronicletimes.com/story/2164930.html|publisher=Cherokee Chronicle Times|accessdate=12 February 2015}}</ref> This expansion was purchased by MidAmerican energy and constructed in 2016 as the 250 MW O'Brien Wind Farm. It also lies in O'Brien county, just to the north of the Highland project.<ref>[http://www.nwestiowa.com/news/wind-stream/article_1c6d06ca-67f6-11e6-93f2-1751ad4b1268.html O'Brien Wind Project]</ref>
