{{More citations needed|date = July 2008}}

A '''Lease Automatic [[Custody transfer|Custody Transfer]] unit''' or '''LACT unit''' measures the net [[volume]] and quality of [[liquid]] [[hydrocarbons]]. A LACT unit measures volumes in the range of 100-7000 [[BOPD]]. This system provides for the automatic measurement, sampling, and transfer of [[petroleum|oil]] from the lease location into a [[Oil pipeline|pipeline]]. A system of this type is applicable where larger volumes of oil are being produced and must have a pipeline available in which to connect.<ref name="Mineral Web: How Oil and Gas is Measured">[http://www.mineralweb.com/oil-and-gas-measurement-a-205.html "How Oil and Gas is Measured"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090712021953/http://www.mineralweb.com/oil-and-gas-measurement-a-205.html |date=2009-07-12 }}, MineralWeb.com.</ref>

